{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.«term_|&gt;ₛ⟨_,_⟩»\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_|&gt;ₛ⟨_,_⟩»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a field specification `𝓕`, and an element `φ` of `𝓕.FieldOp`.\n  The field statistic `fieldOpStatistic φ` is defined to be the statistic associated with\n  the field underlying `φ`.\n\n  The following notation is used in relation to `fieldOpStatistic`:\n- For `φ` an element of `𝓕.FieldOp`, `𝓕 |>ₛ φ` is `fieldOpStatistic φ`.\n- For `φs` a list of `𝓕.FieldOp`, `𝓕 |>ₛ φs` is the product of `fieldOpStatistic φ` over\n  the list `φs`.\n- For a function `f : Fin n → 𝓕.FieldOp` and a finite set `a` of `Fin n`, `𝓕 |>ₛ ⟨f, a⟩` is the\n  product of `fieldOpStatistic (f i)` for all `i ∈ a`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.«term_|>ₛ⟨_,_⟩»","kind":"def","line":132,"name":"FieldSpecification.«term_|>ₛ⟨_,_⟩»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L132-L134"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.«term_|&gt;ₛ__1»\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_|&gt;ₛ__1»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a field specification `𝓕`, and an element `φ` of `𝓕.FieldOp`.\n  The field statistic `fieldOpStatistic φ` is defined to be the statistic associated with\n  the field underlying `φ`.\n\n  The following notation is used in relation to `fieldOpStatistic`:\n- For `φ` an element of `𝓕.FieldOp`, `𝓕 |>ₛ φ` is `fieldOpStatistic φ`.\n- For `φs` a list of `𝓕.FieldOp`, `𝓕 |>ₛ φs` is the product of `fieldOpStatistic φ` over\n  the list `φs`.\n- For a function `f : Fin n → 𝓕.FieldOp` and a finite set `a` of `Fin n`, `𝓕 |>ₛ ⟨f, a⟩` is the\n  product of `fieldOpStatistic (f i)` for all `i ∈ a`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.«term_|>ₛ__1»","kind":"def","line":128,"name":"FieldSpecification.«term_|>ₛ__1»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L128-L130"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.«term_|&gt;ₛ_»\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_|&gt;ₛ_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a field specification `𝓕`, and an element `φ` of `𝓕.FieldOp`.\n  The field statistic `fieldOpStatistic φ` is defined to be the statistic associated with\n  the field underlying `φ`.\n\n  The following notation is used in relation to `fieldOpStatistic`:\n- For `φ` an element of `𝓕.FieldOp`, `𝓕 |>ₛ φ` is `fieldOpStatistic φ`.\n- For `φs` a list of `𝓕.FieldOp`, `𝓕 |>ₛ φs` is the product of `fieldOpStatistic φ` over\n  the list `φs`.\n- For a function `f : Fin n → 𝓕.FieldOp` and a finite set `a` of `Fin n`, `𝓕 |>ₛ ⟨f, a⟩` is the\n  product of `fieldOpStatistic (f i)` for all `i ∈ a`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.«term_|>ₛ_»","kind":"def","line":125,"name":"FieldSpecification.«term_|>ₛ_»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L125-L126"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.fieldOpStatistic\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">fieldOpStatistic</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span> → <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldStatistics/Basic.html#FieldStatistic\">FieldStatistic</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a field specification `𝓕`, and an element `φ` of `𝓕.FieldOp`.\n  The field statistic `fieldOpStatistic φ` is defined to be the statistic associated with\n  the field underlying `φ`.\n\n  The following notation is used in relation to `fieldOpStatistic`:\n- For `φ` an element of `𝓕.FieldOp`, `𝓕 |>ₛ φ` is `fieldOpStatistic φ`.\n- For `φs` a list of `𝓕.FieldOp`, `𝓕 |>ₛ φs` is the product of `fieldOpStatistic φ` over\n  the list `φs`.\n- For a function `f : Fin n → 𝓕.FieldOp` and a finite set `a` of `Fin n`, `𝓕 |>ₛ ⟨f, a⟩` is the\n  product of `fieldOpStatistic (f i)` for all `i ∈ a`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.fieldOpStatistic","kind":"def","line":113,"name":"FieldSpecification.fieldOpStatistic","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L113-L123"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.fieldOpToField\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">fieldOpToField</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.Field\">Field</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a field specification `𝓕`, `𝓕.fieldOpToField` is defined to take field operators\nto their underlying field. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.fieldOpToField","kind":"def","line":106,"name":"FieldSpecification.fieldOpToField","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L106-L111"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.statesIsPosition\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">statesIsPosition</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The bool on `FieldOp` which is true only for position field operator. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.statesIsPosition","kind":"def","line":101,"name":"FieldSpecification.statesIsPosition","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L101-L104"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp.outAsymp\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">FieldOp</span>.<span class=\"name\">outAsymp</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">((<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.Field\">Field</a></span>) × <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.AsymptoticLabel\">AsymptoticLabel</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">f</span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./PhysLean/Units/WithDim/Momentum.html#Momentum\">Momentum</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp.outAsymp","kind":"ctor","line":99,"name":"FieldSpecification.FieldOp.outAsymp","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L99-L99"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp.position\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">FieldOp</span>.<span class=\"name\">position</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">((<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.Field\">Field</a></span>) × <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.PositionLabel\">PositionLabel</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">f</span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./PhysLean/SpaceAndTime/SpaceTime/Basic.html#SpaceTime\">SpaceTime</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp.position","kind":"ctor","line":98,"name":"FieldSpecification.FieldOp.position","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L98-L98"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp.inAsymp\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">FieldOp</span>.<span class=\"name\">inAsymp</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">((<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.Field\">Field</a></span>) × <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.AsymptoticLabel\">AsymptoticLabel</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">f</span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./PhysLean/Units/WithDim/Momentum.html#Momentum\">Momentum</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\">FieldOp</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp.inAsymp","kind":"ctor","line":97,"name":"FieldSpecification.FieldOp.inAsymp","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L97-L97"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">inductive</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">FieldOp</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">𝓕</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For a field specification `𝓕`, the inductive type `𝓕.FieldOp` is defined\n  to contain the following elements:\n- For every `f` in `𝓕.Field`, element of `e` of `AsymptoticLabel f` and `3`-momentum `p`, an\n  element labelled `inAsymp f e p` corresponding to an incoming asymptotic field operator\n  of the field `f`, of label `e` (e.g. specifying the spin), and momentum `p`.\n- For every `f` in `𝓕.Field`, element of `e` of `PositionLabel f` and space-time position `x`, an\n  element labelled `position f e x` corresponding to a position field operator of the field `f`,\n  of label `e` (e.g. specifying the Lorentz index), and position `x`.\n- For every `f` in `𝓕.Field`, element of `e` of `AsymptoticLabel f` and `3`-momentum `p`, an\n  element labelled `outAsymp f e p` corresponding to an outgoing asymptotic field operator of the\n  field `f`, of label `e` (e.g. specifying the spin), and momentum `p`.\n\nAs an example, if `f` corresponds to a Weyl-fermion field, then\n- For `inAsymp f e p`, `e` would correspond to a spin `s`, and `inAsymp f e p` would, once\n  represented in the operator algebra,\n  be proportional to the creation operator `a(p, s)`.\n- `position f e x`, `e` would correspond to a Lorentz index `a`, and `position f e x` would,\n  once represented in the operator algebra, be proportional to the operator\n\n  `∑ s, ∫ d³p/(…) (xₐ(p,s) a(p, s) e ^ (-i p x) + yₐ(p,s) a†(p, s) e ^ (-i p x))`.\n\n- `outAsymp f e p`, `e` would correspond to a spin `s`, and `outAsymp f e p` would,\n  once represented in the operator algebra, be proportional to the\n  annihilation operator `a†(p, s)`.\n\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.FieldOp","kind":"inductive","line":70,"name":"FieldSpecification.FieldOp","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L70-L99"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.statistic\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">statistic</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">self</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.Field\">Field</a></span> → <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldStatistics/Basic.html#FieldStatistic\">FieldStatistic</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For every field `f` in `Field`, the field statistic `statistic f` classifies `f` as either\n`bosonic` or `fermionic`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.statistic","kind":"def","line":65,"name":"FieldSpecification.statistic","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L65-L65"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.AsymptoticLabel\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">AsymptoticLabel</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">self</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.Field\">Field</a></span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For every field `f` in `Field`, the type `AsymptoticLabel f` has elements that label\nthe different asymptotic based field operators associated with the field `f`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.AsymptoticLabel","kind":"def","line":62,"name":"FieldSpecification.AsymptoticLabel","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L62-L62"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.PositionLabel\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">PositionLabel</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">self</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.Field\">Field</a></span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For every field `f` in `Field`, the type `PositionLabel f` has elements that label the\ndifferent position operators associated with the field `f`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.PositionLabel","kind":"def","line":59,"name":"FieldSpecification.PositionLabel","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L59-L59"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.Field\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">Field</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A type whose elements are the constituent fields of the theory. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.Field","kind":"def","line":56,"name":"FieldSpecification.Field","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L56-L56"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.mk\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">Field</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">PositionLabel </span><span class=\"fn\">AsymptoticLabel</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Field</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">statistic</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Field</span> → <a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldStatistics/Basic.html#FieldStatistic\">FieldStatistic</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\">FieldSpecification</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification.mk","kind":"ctor","line":54,"name":"FieldSpecification.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L54-L54"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification\"><span class=\"name\">FieldSpecification</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> 1</div></div>","info":{"doc":"The structure `FieldSpecification` is defined to have the following content:\n- A type `Field` whose elements are the constituent fields of the theory.\n- For every field `f` in `Field`, a type `PositionLabel f` whose elements label the different\n  position operators associated with the field `f`. For example,\n  - For `f` a *real-scalar field*, `PositionLabel f` will have a unique element.\n  - For `f` a *complex-scalar field*, `PositionLabel f` will have two elements, one for the field\n    operator and one for its conjugate.\n  - For `f` a *Dirac fermion*, `PositionLabel f` will have eight elements, one for each Lorentz\n    index of the field and its conjugate.\n  - For `f` a *Weyl fermion*, `PositionLabel f` will have four elements, one for each Lorentz\n    index of the field and its conjugate.\n- For every field `f` in `Field`, a type `AsymptoticLabel f` whose elements label the different\n  types of incoming asymptotic field operators associated with the\n  field `f` (this also matches the types of outgoing asymptotic field operators).\n  For example,\n  - For `f` a *real-scalar field*, `AsymptoticLabel f` will have a unique element.\n  - For `f` a *complex-scalar field*, `AsymptoticLabel f` will have two elements, one for the\n    field operator and one for its conjugate.\n  - For `f` a *Dirac fermion*, `AsymptoticLabel f` will have four elements, two for each spin.\n  - For `f` a *Weyl fermion*, `AsymptoticLabel f` will have two elements, one for each spin.\n- For each field `f` in `Field`, a field statistic `statistic f` which classifies `f` as either\n  `bosonic` or `fermionic`.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/QFT/PerturbationTheory/FieldSpecification/Basic.html#FieldSpecification","kind":"structure","line":30,"name":"FieldSpecification","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L30-L65"}}],"imports":["Init","PhysLean.SpaceAndTime.SpaceTime.Basic","PhysLean.Units.WithDim.Momentum","PhysLean.QFT.PerturbationTheory.FieldStatistics.OfFinset"],"instances":[],"name":"PhysLean.QFT.PerturbationTheory.FieldSpecification.Basic"}